==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Album
<hw>Al"bum</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., neut. of
<ets>albus</ets> white: cf. F. <ets>album</ets>. Cf.
<er>Alb</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A white
tablet on which anything was inscribed, as a list of names,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A register for visitors' names; a visitors'
book.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A blank book, in which to insert autographs,
sketches, memorial writing of friends, photographs, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Albumen</ent>⟦br⟧
